                     Armour-Geddon Command Key Summary
                               by Excalibur


Note: Most of the commands work on all the vehicles... Some may be only for
      a specific vehicle.
 
S - Starts the engine
+ - Increases speed
- - Decreases speed
HELP - Raises shields
DEL - Lowers shields
Q - Selects first weapon
A - Selects second weapon
Z - Selects third weapon
P - Pauses
T - Toggles next target when using missiles or rockets
1-5 - Beacons (Waypoints)
7 - Waypoint range
8 - Base range
Tab - Moves cannon up
Ctrl - Moves cannon down
Right Alt - Fires flares
Space bar - Toggles between mouse and joystick
< - Left rudder, turns plane left
> - Right rudder, turns plane right


F1-F6 takes you back to the menu. You can bring out another vehicle. To get 
back to your first vehicle, chose it from the 'roster' and click on the go  
pilot window.


Views: (Using keypad)

Enter - External view 1
. - External view 2
0 - Satellite view (+ zooms out / - zooms in).
1-4, 6-9 - Shows different views - Works inside and outside of the cockpit.
           Press shift 1-4, 6-9 and it will go immediately to that view.
5 - Toggles between the cockpit view and the previous external view.
    (Shift 5 does the same thing).
/ - Moves the point of view closer (Outside vehicle; External views 1, 2).
* - Moves the point of view farther away (Outside vehicle; External views
    1, 2).
( - Turns to the right (Outside vehicle; External views 1, 2).
) - Turns to the left (Outside vehicle; External views 1, 2).


* While viewing from either external views, + moves the point of view up in
  elevation, and - moves the point of view down in elevation.

Note: You can change to external views while the vehicles are being raised
      up on the platform. You can also watch from the cockpit as your
      vehicle is being raised ONLY after your vehicle as 'appeared' by
      pressing 5 on the keypad. Pressing either the 5, 0, ., or Enter key
      on the keypad from the cockpit view to external view and back will
      return back to the previous cockpit view.
